content: Back in NYC! The energy here is electric. Still, the job hunt begins anew. Anyone know where the best coffee is around here?
Just turned 22. Reflecting on the year, I've learned that setbacks are just setups for comebacks. Now, back to coding my personal trading algo.
Spent the last few days diving into AI-driven code evolution. It's like tuning a piano—precision is everything.
Had a great chat with an old mentor over coffee. He gave some solid advice on how to approach quant firms. Now, to refine my pitch.
My trading algorithm now integrates blockchain for real-time insights. It’s rough around the edges, but it's a start.
My algo crashed during a simulated market test. Time to debug and find where the inefficiencies lie.
